parameters:
\N<Customer>Heh... hey, shopkeeper. You remember our deal from the other
time, right...?

\N<Shopkeeper>Ah, indeed. I did think it would be fine for her to go a bit
further for our valued customers.

\N<Shopkeeper>But, you haven't forgotten, have you? I did say that it
would naturally cost quite a bit more for that.
\N<Customer>Heh... of course. I've been saving up just for this day...
\N<Customer>So? What should I do? What's the procedure?

\N<Shopkeeper>What are you talking about? There's no particular procedure.
It's all up to your discretion.
\N<Customer>Huh? Then what exactly am I supposed to do?

\N<Shopkeeper>If you think about it, there are plenty of ways. For
example, you could get her drunk without her noticing.

\N<Shopkeeper>You should figure that out on your own. You want to bed her,
right? Then you can't leave it to others.

\N<Customer>Hmph... fine by me, we'll do it our way then. But let me
warn you, don't regret it if she ends up broken.

\N<Shopkeeper>I can't overlook that. She's our precious waitress,
remember? I'd prefer if you treat her with the utmost care.

\N<Customer>Heh... selling her off behind her back and still saying
that, huh.
